      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation workflow with independent review of model setup by a second analyst.",
      "rationale": "A standardized simulation workflow document was followed by all three modeling teams (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes). Cross-team review sessions confirmed consistent boundary condition application and material property assignment. Achieved level 3 exceeds requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form uncertainty quantified and shown to be within acceptable bounds for the quantity of interest.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic isotropic constitutive model was selected for titanium alloy pedicle screws. Literature supports this model form for static loading below yield. Sensitivity analysis confirmed model form uncertainty contribution to construct stiffness prediction is less than 4%. Achieved level 3 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs derived from measurements on test specimens with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy elastic modulus (114 GPa) and Poisson ratio (0.34) sourced from certified material test reports for the specific lot used in physical testing. Screw geometry digitized from coordinate measuring machine data. Input uncertainty propagated through Monte Carlo analysis. Achieved level 3 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples are representative of the device population and lot certification is available.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All samples sourced from the same manufacturing lot with full traceability. Sample size exceeds ASTM F1717 minimum requirement. Achieved level 3 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of loading scenarios relevant to the intended use.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single compression-bending load condition as specified in ASTM F1717. While this condition is the standard regulatory benchmark, it does not cover the full range of in vivo loading scenarios. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 3; this gap is acknowledged as a limitation of the current validation dataset."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA input parameters demonstrably correspond to measured experimental conditions.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions in the FEA replicated the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry and applied load point as measured from the physical test setup. Load application angle and fixture compliance were incorporated from direct measurement. Achieved level 3 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric defined a priori with acceptance threshold documented before results examined.",
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest (construct stiffness at 2% offset) was compared using the u95 validation metric per ASME V&V 20. FEA predictions from all three modeling teams fell within the experimental uncertainty band for 10 of 11 constructs. The single outlier was investigated and attributed to a manufacturing anomaly in one test specimen. Achieved level 3 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest are directly linked to the clinical or regulatory question being addressed.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and peak screw bending moment are the quantities of interest. Both are directly specified in ASTM F1717 as regulatory submission endpoints and are mechanistically linked to implant fatigue performance. Achieved level 3 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities address the same device geometry, loading mode, and material system as the intended computational use.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw geometry, UHMWPE block test medium, and static compression-bending protocol as the intended FEA application. The three-team ensemble approach strengthens confidence in cross-laboratory reproducibility. Achieved level 3 meets requirement."
    }
